  "text": "There are a range of other error measures in the multiple testing literature, including the FWER, k-FWER, FDR, generalized FDR, marginal FDR, positive FDR, FDX, false cluster rate, weighted FDR, overall FDR, outer-node FDR, and focus-level FDR. These concepts are useful but may cause confusion. [CITATION_1] provided a good summary of error measures and discussed how to match proper error rates with inference needs.",
